#: ../../../networking/diagnostic/twisted_pair_layer1_diagnostics.rst:328
msgid ""
"Use `ethtool` to test for physical layer issues such as cable faults. The "
"test results can vary depending on the cable's condition, the technology in "
"use, and the state of the link partner. The results from the cable test will "
"help in diagnosing issues like open circuits, shorts, impedance mismatches, "
"and noise-related problems."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../networking/diagnostic/twisted_pair_layer1_diagnostics.rst:334
msgid "**Command:** `ethtool --cable-test <interface>`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../networking/diagnostic/twisted_pair_layer1_diagnostics.rst:336
msgid ""
"The following are the typical outputs for **Single-Pair Ethernet (SPE)** and "
"**Multi-Pair Ethernet (MPE)**:"
